912
01:42:49,365 --> 01:42:58,852
So we wanted to just take a minute to talk about some of the key discussion topics that have come up in these meetings.

913
01:42:59,787 --> 01:43:03,049
So one of the first ones is related to density and height.

914
01:43:05,169 --> 01:43:21,517
So as part of the redevelopment of Waukland Court, one of the goals that the Medford Housing Authority has, and that's also included in the city of Medford housing production plan is to increase the number of affordable housing units on site.

915
01:43:22,460 --> 01:43:35,502
And so as part of the design, there will be the 144 existing units that are being replaced, but there would also be 94 net new units on site.

916
01:43:36,383 --> 01:43:46,185
All of those would be deeply affordable, and that would be expected to increase the number of residents on site by approximately 101%, and that's based on

917
01:43:50,033 --> 01:43:56,219
average occupancy rates of the Medford Housing Authority has for variety unit types.

918
01:43:57,680 --> 01:44:07,089
In terms of the height of the different buildings on site, you know, the senior mid-rise, which essentially has five stories of living space,

919
01:44:08,380 --> 01:44:21,968
with the first story that is dedicated entirely to covered parking for senior disabled residents, as well as extensive new community space.

920
01:44:22,968 --> 01:44:25,910
The family mid-rise itself is four stories.

921
01:44:27,231 --> 01:44:35,415
And the height here is needed because one of the key goals of the project is to provide elevator access to not just

922
01:44:37,243 --> 01:44:46,326
elderly disabled residents, but as well to families, that's a really rare building typology that is needed in the city.

923
01:44:46,346 --> 01:44:56,069
And this will essentially allow residents who have accessibility needs to age in place and stay in these properties longer.

924
01:44:57,549 --> 01:45:10,313
But in addition to that, the more efficient footprint coupled with the height allows for more programmable and accessible open space outside of the buildings.

925
01:45:10,574 --> 01:45:26,319
And then the way that the design team has been working through the addition of this density and height on site is by very carefully placing it so that different building typologies or building types, mid-rise,

926
01:45:26,970 --> 01:45:33,273
is next to adjacent uses that are complementary or reflect similar heights and densities.

927
01:45:33,413 --> 01:45:42,738
So for example, senior mid-rise isn't being placed next to the two-story residential homes along North Street and Auburn Street.

928
01:45:44,697 --> 01:45:51,922
That brings us to the next topic, which is the proximity to the railroad track of the senior mid-rise building.

929
01:45:53,163 --> 01:46:06,153
So these buildings that are currently on site were built in 1963 when both standards of construction were much lower in terms of noise, but also building materials.

930
01:46:07,514 --> 01:46:10,696
The current facade is being designed

931
01:46:11,615 --> 01:46:16,258
to meet HUD noise requirements, which are much stricter today than they were back in 1963.

932
01:46:17,038 --> 01:46:29,245
And we have an acoustical engineer on the design team who has provided recommendations in terms of how to detail that facade in order to meet those HUD noise requirements.

933
01:46:29,385 --> 01:46:34,869
That includes using high-performance windows, as well as additional insulation.

934
01:46:36,388 --> 01:46:45,590
So based on that, our expectation is that noise will be greatly improved from what residents currently experience today.

935
01:46:45,610 --> 01:47:02,434
And it's also important that as part of this redevelopment, we're providing high quality units that have central AC and that also have mechanical ventilation to ensure that people have good environmental air quality indoors.

936
01:47:03,715 --> 01:47:23,605
And as we just saw with the other project that came before us for the amendment to their site plan review, there are many examples of comparable buildings that are placed adjacent to railroad tracks, especially now that there's more emphasis on building transit oriented developments like Rockland Court.

