945
01:48:42,667 --> 01:48:51,611
And this is based on usage for low-income seniors and families that MHA has as part of their portfolio.

946
01:48:52,731 --> 01:49:01,095
And we also had a traffic impact survey done by Niche Engineering to look at any kind of traffic impacts of the new development

947
01:49:01,614 --> 01:49:07,136
and they determined that no traffic mitigation measures were warranted for this project.

948
01:49:08,976 --> 01:49:14,958
The final issue that I'm going to bring up is related to environmental issues.

949
01:49:15,939 --> 01:49:26,782
So the site is built on urban fill, and as part of the pre-development, we had a phase one and a phase two environmental site assessment done.

950
01:49:27,594 --> 01:49:36,320
And these site assessments found a variety of different contaminants that are pretty typical to a site that is made out of urban fill.

951
01:49:37,621 --> 01:49:44,126
So that means that as part of this redevelopment, there will be asbestos remediation, as well as soil removal.

952
01:49:44,866 --> 01:49:47,868
Those will have to meet state and federal requirements.

953
01:49:48,169 --> 01:49:55,554
And during construction, there will be monitoring to ensure that hazardous materials are properly handled.

954
01:49:56,414 --> 01:49:57,055
And lastly,

955
01:49:58,210 --> 01:50:09,733
There's no environmental impact statement that's needed for this project because the project does not meet any of the Massachusetts Environmental Protection Act thresholds.

956
01:50:09,993 --> 01:50:12,534
They're not exceeded as part of this project.

957
01:50:16,775 --> 01:50:20,116
So that brings us to the overview of the PDD process.

958
01:50:20,656 --> 01:50:27,538
So, Walkland Court is currently designed as, or not designed, it's currently zoned as apartment one.

