01:50:55,129 --> 01:50:57,972
We submitted that PDD application on August 8th,

961
01:50:58,898 --> 01:51:03,921
of this year, had the first Community Development Board hearing on September 6.

962
01:51:04,182 --> 01:51:10,706
It then went to the City Council, who then referred it back to the CDB on September 19.

963
01:51:11,567 --> 01:51:26,357
And throughout this process, we've been working with the city and their attorney, Jonathan Silverstein, on the PDD3 zoning amendment, which I will now pass it on to our Council, Hannah Kilson, to describe in greater detail.

964
01:51:27,380 --> 01:51:29,162
Hannah Kilson, BOEB, she, her, hers, and hers.

965
01:51:42,544 --> 01:51:44,565
in Boston at 84 State Street.

966
01:51:45,366 --> 01:51:56,953
I want to do an overview of the zoning amendment and respond to the opening request of us, which was to give you context against current zoning.

967
01:51:58,374 --> 01:52:06,399
To begin, I'd like to make the point that the purpose for the PDD-3 and PDDs in general is to give

968
01:52:07,851 --> 01:52:23,362
Developers, the necessary flexibility right to redevelop and in this case, the housing authority, the ability to redevelop walk in court site so that it can address the shortage of accessible and affordable housing in Medford.

969
01:52:23,982 --> 01:52:37,274
So, the 1st element to remark on this PDD 3 zoning amendment is the permitted uses that will be made available on the site as a result of the PDD.

970
01:52:38,715 --> 01:52:42,018
So, the PDD would only have residential uses.

971
01:52:42,843 --> 01:52:47,384
and an accessory general office uses permitted on the site.

972
01:52:47,444 --> 01:52:51,606
There would be no other types of uses allowed on the site.

973
01:52:52,406 --> 01:53:11,752
The proposed PDD provides that the following uses are permitted as of right, which are the detached single-family dwelling, the attached single-family dwelling, the detached two-family dwelling, both class A and class B multiple dwellings,

974
01:53:12,492 --> 01:53:15,734
and senior housing independent living facility.

975
01:53:16,614 --> 01:53:30,622
Currently class B multiple dwellings are not permitted in an apartment one district and nor are and all senior housing facilities require a special permit.

976
01:53:31,283 --> 01:53:38,767
So the this which the PDD would allow for the development of the of the site for a class B

977
01:53:39,461 --> 01:53:44,764
multiple dwelling, which is one which has no more than 75 feet and six stories.

978
01:53:45,464 --> 01:54:05,635
There would be residential uses that would be permitted by special permit, and those are noted here with dormitory fraternity and sorority houses, lodging and boarding houses, and other senior housing facilities, which are also currently in an apartment one district permitted by special permit.

979
01:54:08,785 --> 01:54:22,156
And then the other use, as I noted at the beginning, was that there would be accessory general office use would be permitted as of right associated with the residential use.

980
01:54:22,476 --> 01:54:31,923
And this permitted use would enable the management offices to be located within the multifamily dwelling for the development.

981
01:54:32,668 --> 01:54:34,011
So that's residential uses.

982
01:54:34,852 --> 01:54:38,540
I'd like to turn now to talk about the dimensional

983
01:54:39,080 --> 01:54:52,828
provisions in the PDD amendment, which as I noted before, really give the project the flexibility needed to build this highly needed type of housing in Medford.

984
01:54:53,689 --> 01:55:03,715
